TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {11031=Chelsea Hunt, right, a member of Kane Middle School's track and field team, set a new seventh grade record at Saturday's Johnsonburg Invitational. Chelsea, pictured here with coach Stacy Beagle, won the 1600-meter run in a time of 5:49.53, breaking the old KMS standard of 5:54, set by Dani Kocjancic in 2005., 16159=Savannah Anderson tied the Kane High School record for the pole vault. The Lady Wolves' senior cleared 10'0" at the West Central Coaches Classic in Altoona on Friday, tying the mark set by Angela Salerno in 2007. Anderson and her teammates will be back in action this afternoon when they travel to Johnsonburg., 5980=Patrick Anderson, a 2012 Kane High graduate pictured here during an indoor track meet earlier this year, placed fifth at last weekend's Bucknell Classic as a member of Penn State's track and field team. The Nittany Lions' redshirt sophomore cleared a personal best 15'9" in the meet., 4240=Alyssa Zampogna set the new KHS sophomore record for the long jump during Tuesday's meet in Bradford. Zampogna's leap of 15'8 1/2" broke the previous standard set by Taylor Bucheit in 2012. Bucheit set the mark by jumping 15'1" as a 10th-grader. The compiling of sophomore track and field records date back to 1996, according to coach Jim Sirianni. Zampogna and the rest of the KHS track and field teams will travel to Brookville tomorrow to take part in the Raiders' annual invitational., 12907=Three Kane Middle School track team members broke existing school records last week in Sheffield. Rachael Buhl, left, broke the seventh grade record in the 100-meter hurdles with a time of 19.43. Jake Alcorn reset his own record in the triple jump with a leap of 32'7.5", while Chelsea Hunt, right, broke the record she set last week in the 1600 meter run with a time of 5:48.5 and also tied the 800-meter record, 2:41.1., 17925=Kelsey Johnson, a 2014 Kane High graduate is a member of Clarion University's Girls Track team. Johnson competed at the PSAC Championships last weekend at East Stroudsburg University. Johnson ran on Clarion's 4x400 meter relay team, which finished eighth. The former Lady Wolves standout turned in a PR with a split time of 61.0.}
